#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!CDarkGreen #!N 
 #!Rall19 AutoAxes Configuration #!N #!EC #!N #!N The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoAxes Configuration 
#!EF dialog box allows you to generate a set of axes 
for an object in the Image window and to specify some 
of its characteristics. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 
1. Click on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF in the menu bar of 
the Image window and then select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoAxes #!EF in the 
pull-down menu. The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoAxes Configuration #!EF dialog box appears. Note: 
To display additional options, click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Expand #!EF button 
at the bottom of the dialog box. For purposes of this 
tutorial, you will not be changing any  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoAxes #!EF options. 
For more information, see  #!Lautoaxe,dxall770 h AutoAxes  #!EL  in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's 
Reference. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Enabled #!EF 
toggle button (at the top of the dialog box) to select 
the AutoAxes option. The button is now activated. #!N #!I30 #!N 
3. Click on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   OK #!EF or  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Apply #!EF at 
the bottom of the dialog box to confirm the selection. #!N 
#!N #!I0 #!N Notes: #!N #!I30 #!N a.  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   OK #!EF 
closes the dialog box;  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Apply #!EF does not. #!N #!I30 
#!N b. Selection of  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Enabled #!EF and  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   OK #!EF 
or  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Apply #!EF is necessary but not sufficient to activate 
the AutoAxes option (see next step). #!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!I30 
#!N 4. Select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute #!EF in the menu bar and 
then  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute Once #!EF in the pull-down menu. #!N #!N 
The object now appears in an axes box. Because the view 
is "head on," the box appears to be 2-dimensional. For  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Diagonal #!EF or any of the "Off" views, however, it appears 
fully 3-dimensional (see next step). #!N #!I30 #!N 5. To change 
the view of the object, select another (e.g.,  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Diagonal #!EF 
) from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Set View #!EF pull-down list in the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control... #!EF dialog box. The view changes to  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Diagonal #!EF (note that the axes box changes as well). #!N 
#!I30 #!N 6. To remove the axes box from the window: 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N a. Deactivate the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Enabled #!EF toggle button in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoAxes Configuration #!EF 
dialog box by clicking on it. #!N #!I30 #!N b. Click 
on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   OK #!EF or  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Apply #!EF . #!N #!I30 
#!N c. Again, execute the program (unless it is already in 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute on Change #!EF mode). The axes box disappears. #!N 
#!I30 #!N d. To restore the original view of the object, 
click on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Reset #!EF in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control #!EF 
dialog box #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 7. 
Close the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control #!EF dialog box (by clicking on 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Close #!EF ) and the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   AutoAxes Configuration #!EF dialog 
box (by clicking on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Cancel #!EF ). #!N #!I0 #!N 
#!EF #!N #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rvcrcont7 #!N Graphics omitted from Online 
Documentation. Please see the manual. #!N #!N Figure 7. Sequence Control 
Panel. The first two buttons at top left are Loop and 
Palindrome. The others are: Step (<  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   || #!EF >), Counter 
(  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   ... #!EF ), Back (<), Forward (>), Stop (&sqbul.), 
and Pause (  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   || #!EF ). #!EF #!N #!EC #!N 
